## Stage Handoff Formats

Each stage produces a structured document passed to the next.

### Context Doc (Stage 1 → Stage 2)

```markdown
# Context: {request one-liner}

## Request
{verbatim original request}

## Affected files
- `src/path/file.py` — {role, why affected}

## Dependency Impact
For each changed interface/schema/response, list all consumers that must be updated:
| Changed component | Consumers | Update needed? |
|---|---|---|
| `src/.../api.py` function | `static/js/app.js` fetch call | Yes / No + reason |
| Pydantic response schema | tests, UI field access | Yes / No + reason |
| OpenSearch mapping | indexing_service, seed scripts | Yes / No + reason |
| env var / config | Dockerfile, .env.example, docs | Yes / No + reason |

## External dependencies
- {OpenSearch index / MongoDB collection / API}

## Constraints
- {relevant rules from .cursor/rules/}

## Clarifying questions
{list or "None"}
```

### Spec Doc (Stage 2 → Stage 3 + Stage 4)

```markdown
# Spec: {feature name}

## Goal
{one sentence}

## Affected layers
| Module | Layer | Change |
|---|---|---|

## Interfaces
```python
def function_name(arg: Type) -> ReturnType: ...
```

## File plan
- CREATE `src/...` — purpose
- MODIFY `src/...` — what changes

## Dependency coverage
For each item in Context Doc Dependency Impact table — state what was done:
| Consumer | Decision | File in plan? |
|---|---|---|
| `static/js/app.js` | updated fetch field access | Yes — line in file plan |
| `tests/unit/...` | fixture unchanged, schema compatible | No — reason stated |

## Acceptance criteria
- [ ] criterion
```

### Implementation Summary (Stage 3 → Stage 4)

```markdown
# Implementation: {feature name}

## Files changed
- `src/...` — {what changed}

## Spec deviations
{any, or "None"}

## Lint
{output of `uv run ruff check .`}
```

### Review Result (Stage 4 → Stage 5)

```markdown
# Review: {feature name}

## Result: ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL

## Checks
- [ ] Satisfies original request
- [ ] Follows .cursor/rules/
- [ ] Matches spec (interfaces, files, acceptance criteria)
- [ ] Lint passes
- [ ] Dependency Impact items from Context Doc are addressed (each consumer updated or
      explicitly skipped with reason — no silent omissions)

## Issues (if FAIL)
{specific issue — rule file reference}
```

