## Model Selection per Stage

All subagents (Stages 1–4) inherit the model of the parent chat — **never pass `model:` parameter** when launching via `Task` tool. This ensures every stage runs on the same model as the main conversation.

| Stage | Model | Note |
|---|---|---|
| Stage 1 — Context | inherited | Omit `model:` — inherits from parent |
| Stage 2 — Architect | inherited | Omit `model:` — inherits from parent |
| Stage 3 — Implementer | inherited | Omit `model:` — inherits from parent |
| Stage 4 — Reviewer | inherited | Omit `model:` — inherits from parent |
| Stage 5 — Knowledge Update | main chat | Already in orchestrator session |

```python
# ❌ NEVER — hardcodes a specific model for subagents
Task(subagent_type="generalPurpose", model="fast", ...)

# ✅ CORRECT — omit model so subagent inherits parent model
Task(subagent_type="generalPurpose", ...)
```

